{"questionId":"13338","questionHtml":"<p>Given that <em>П</em><sub>1</sub> and <em>П</em><sub>2</sub> meet in a line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span>, verify that the vector equation of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span> can be&nbsp;given by <em><strong>r</strong></em>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {\\frac{5}{4}} \\\\   0 \\\\   { - \\frac{7}{4}}  \\end{array}} \\right) + \\lambda \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {\\frac{1}{2}} \\\\   1 \\\\   { - \\frac{5}{2}}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>5</mn>\n                <mn>4</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>7</mn>\n                <mn>4</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>5</mn>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>substitution of equation of line into both equations of planes&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\\left( {\\frac{5}{4} + \\frac{\\lambda }{2}} \\right) + \\left( { - \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{{5\\lambda }}{2}} \\right) = 2\">\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>5</mn>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>λ</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>7</mn>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n          <mi>λ</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{5}{4} + \\frac{\\lambda }{2}} \\right) - 3\\lambda&nbsp; - \\left( { - \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{{5\\lambda }}{2}} \\right) = 3\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>5</mn>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>λ</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>7</mn>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n          <mi>λ</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>adding <em>Π</em><sub>1</sub> and <em>Π</em><sub>2</sub> gives&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4x - 2y = 5\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>given&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = \\lambda&nbsp; \\Rightarrow x = \\frac{5}{4} + \\frac{\\lambda }{2}\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>λ</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z = 2 - y - 3x =&nbsp; - \\frac{7}{4} - \\frac{{5\\lambda }}{2}\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mi>λ</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>⇒<em><strong>r</strong></em>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {\\frac{5}{4}} \\\\&nbsp; 0 \\\\&nbsp; { - \\frac{7}{4}}&nbsp; \\end{array}} \\right) + \\lambda \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {\\frac{1}{2}} \\\\&nbsp; 1 \\\\&nbsp; { - \\frac{5}{2}}&nbsp; \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>5</mn>\n                <mn>4</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>7</mn>\n                <mn>4</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>λ</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>5</mn>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD&nbsp;3</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>n</strong></em><sub>1</sub>&nbsp;× <em><strong>n</strong></em><sub>2</sub> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  2 \\\\   4 \\\\   { - 10}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 4\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {\\frac{1}{2}} \\\\   1 \\\\   { - \\frac{5}{2}}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>5</mn>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>common point&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{5}{4} - 3\\left( 0 \\right) - \\left( { - \\frac{7}{4}} \\right) = 3\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>7</mn>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 3\\left( {\\frac{5}{4}} \\right) - 0 - \\left( { - \\frac{7}{4}} \\right) =&nbsp; - 2\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>5</mn>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>7</mn>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13338","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_11b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that П1 and П2 meet in a line L , verify that the vector equation of L can be given by r = ( 5 4 0 − 7 4 ) + λ ( 1 2 1 − 5 2 ) .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}